            . I took up the prisoner, and had him with Mr. Abdy in his compting-house. He did not care to speak at all for some time; at last he said, he did take the silver, and begged forgiveness, and said, it was the first fact.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I was at work at the time this silver was brought to be sold. I know nothing about it.</p>
